  "description": [
    "Vol 63 No 27 106th NJS Class Sees 239 Graduate One of the largest classes of the US Naval Justice School in recent years was graduated Wednesday at Family Theatre Chief Judge Robert E Quinn US Court of Military Appeals addressed 239 students graduat ing from the 106th class of the School Chief Judge Quinn spoke on the relationship between the Court anti the Uniform Code of Military Justice Naval Service Prior to his appointment to the Court by President Truman in 1951 Chief Judge Quinn was ac tive in the Navy and in public life in Rhode Island His Navy positions inlude service as legal Officer of the First Naval Dis trict during World War II From 1937 to 1939 he served as gover nor of Rhode Island Class There were 23 Navy lawyers in the officer class The remainder of the officer class was composts of 113 Navy officers eight offi cers of the Marine Corps and two from the Coast Guard The enlisted class consisted of 47 Navymen ten Marines IS from the Army 17 from the Air Force and one Coast Guardsman Navy Official Visits NUOS Tours Plant CAPT S N Anastasion of the Office of"
